{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01296hqdccYdxXQvHm34P29X","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /tmp/change-plan-nginx.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"57d630fa-3e46-44c6-b94f-65bf71933d7b","uuid":"7d458c54-bacf-4196-b26d-39c43595e62e","timestamp":"2026-06-18T09:33:44.390Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/tmp/change-plan-nginx.md","content":"# ingress-nginx Controller Upgrade — Change / Migration Plan\n\nStatus: DRAFT FOR REVIEW. No changes applied. Live cluster left exactly as found.\n\n## 1. Current state (as inspected)\n\n- Controller Deployment: `ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller`, replicas=1,\n  RollingUpdate (maxSurge 25%, maxUnavailable 1).\n- Image (digest-pinned):\n  `registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1@sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47`\n  (nginx 1.27.1). Kubernetes server is v1.35.\n- IngressClass: `nginx`, controller `k8s.io/ingress-nginx`, NOT marked default\n  (no `ingressclass.kubernetes.io/is-default-class` annotation).\n- Controller container args (verbatim):\n  - `--election-id=ingress-nginx-leader`\n  - `--controller-class=k8s.io/ingress-nginx`\n  - `--ingress-class=nginx`\n  - `--configmap=$(POD_NAMESPACE)/ingress-nginx-controller`\n  - `--validating-webhook=:8443`\n  - `--validating-webhook-certificate=/usr/local/certificates/cert`\n  - `--validating-webhook-key=/usr/local/certificates/key`\n  - `--watch-ingress-without-class=true`   <-- see issue #1\n  - `--publish-status-address=localhost`   <-- see issue #2\n  - `--watch-ingress-without-class=false`  <-- duplicate; last value wins\n- ConfigMap `ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller`: present but `data` is\n  empty/null (no custom nginx tunables set).\n- Ports: hostPort 80/443 (host port binding) + webhook 8443.\n- `terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0` (no graceful drain on pod shutdown).\n- Validating admission webhook enabled (cert from secret `ingress-nginx-admission`).\n- demo namespace: `demo-app` Deployment (1 replica) running, plus a `curl-test`\n  pod. NO Service and NO Ingress object currently exist in `demo` — the app is\n  not actually reachable through the controller yet (no Ingress routes it).\n\n## 2. Issues / risks to resolve as part of the upgrade\n\n1. **Duplicate, conflicting flag** `--watch-ingress-without-class` appears twice\n   (`=true` then `=false`). The last occurrence wins, so the effective behavior is\n   `false` (only Ingresses explicitly using class `nginx` are served). This is\n   confusing and fragile. DECISION REQUIRED: keep `=false` (recommended; remove the\n   stale `=true` line) or intentionally watch class-less Ingresses (`=true`).\n2. **`--publish-status-address=localhost`** publishes `localhost` as the status\n   address on Ingress objects' `.status.loadBalancer`. This is almost certainly a\n   leftover from a single-node/dev setup and is wrong for a real LB/node-IP setup.\n   Re-evaluate; set to the real LB address or remove and use a proper Service.\n3. **`terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0`** means in-flight requests are dropped on\n   rollout. For an upgrade with zero/minimal downtime, raise this (e.g. 30–300s)\n   and rely on the `/wait-shutdown` preStop hook.\n4. **replicas=1** — a single controller pod means an outage window during the\n   rolling upgrade. Consider scaling to 2 with a PodDisruptionBudget before upgrade.\n5. **Empty controller ConfigMap** — no custom tunables today, so nothing to\n   migrate here, but confirm none are expected post-upgrade.\n6. **demo app not wired up** — no Service/Ingress in `demo`. If exposure is\n   intended, that wiring must be added (out of scope for the controller upgrade,\n   but flag it).\n\n## 3. Pre-upgrade checklist\n\n- [ ] Confirm target controller version (e.g. latest 1.x; review the upstream\n      changelog between v1.14.1 and target for breaking changes / removed flags /\n      API deprecations).\n- [ ] Verify Kubernetes v1.35 is within the target controller's supported matrix.\n- [ ] Back up live state:\n      `kubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml > backup-deploy.yaml`\n      `kubectl -n ingress-nginx get configmap ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml > backup-cm.yaml`\n      `kubectl get ingressclass nginx -o yaml > backup-ingressclass.yaml`\n      `kubectl get validatingwebhookconfigurations -l app.kubernetes.io/name=ingress-nginx -o yaml > backup-webhook.yaml`\n- [ ] Record current digest so rollback is exact:\n      `v1.14.1@sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47`.\n- [ ] Snapshot the rendered nginx config: `kubectl -n ingress-nginx exec <pod> -- cat /etc/nginx/nginx.conf`.\n\n## 4. Upgrade steps (to be executed in the maintenance window — NOT done here)\n\n1. (Optional resilience) Scale controller to 2 replicas and add a PDB\n   `minAvailable: 1` so the rolling upgrade never drops to zero pods.\n2. Set `terminationGracePeriodSeconds` to e.g. 300 on the controller pod template.\n3. Clean up the args list: remove the stale `--watch-ingress-without-class=true`\n   line (keep a single, intentional value); re-evaluate `--publish-status-address`.\n4. Update the controller image to the approved target version, digest-pinned.\n   Keep `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`.\n5. If the target version ships an updated admission webhook / RBAC / IngressClass\n   manifest, apply those (typically via the matching release manifest or Helm\n   chart values) BEFORE/with the controller bump.\n6. Apply changes and watch the rollout:\n   `kubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller`.\n7. Confirm a clean backend reload in the controller logs (\"Backend successfully\n   reloaded\", no config errors) and that the validating webhook is serving.\n\n## 5. Post-upgrade verification\n\n- [ ] `kubectl -n ingress-nginx get pods` — controller Ready, no restarts/crashloops.\n- [ ] Controller logs show the new `Release:` version and a successful reload.\n- [ ] Admission webhook works: a test Ingress create is validated (and rejected\n      when malformed).\n- [ ] End-to-end traffic test through the controller for the demo app (once it is\n      wired with a Service + Ingress) returns the expected response.\n- [ ] `kubectl get ingress -A` shows the expected `ADDRESS`/status entries.\n\n## 6. Rollback plan\n\n- Re-apply the digest-pinned previous image\n  (`v1.14.1@sha256:f95a79b...e47`) to the Deployment, or\n  `kubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout undo deploy/ingress-nginx-controller`.\n- Re-apply the backed-up Deployment, ConfigMap, IngressClass, and webhook YAML if\n  any of those were changed.\n- Verify rollout status and a clean backend reload as in section 5.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
